🔹 1. Last 50 log lines from running container web

✅ docker logs web --tail 50
👉 Directly shows last 50 logs from container logs.

🔹 2. Undo most recent commit but keep work locally

✅ git reset --soft HEAD~1
👉 --soft keeps changes staged.
❌ --hard delete करतो changes, ❌ revert new commit बनवतो.

🔹 3. Show mounted filesystems (human-readable)

✅ df -h
👉 -h = human readable (MB/GB).

🔹 4. Safest way to remove only one IAM role

✅ terraform destroy -target=aws_iam_role.my_role
👉 Destroys only targeted resource.

🔹 5. Update K8s deployment image (without editing YAML)

✅ kubectl set image deployment/app app=myrepo/app:2.0
👉 Direct rolling update of image.

🔹 6. EC2 → Access S3 without credentials

✅ IAM Role with S3 policy
👉 Best practice: attach IAM Role to EC2.

🔹 7. Jenkins job stuck in “Waiting for next available executor”

✅ *Manage Nodes & Clouds* to see whether agents are offline
👉 First check → are executors available?

🔹 8. Show 5 processes using most memory

✅ ps aux --sort=-%mem | head -n 6
👉 Sort by memory, show top 5 (plus header).

🔹 9. Show last 50 log lines for systemd service

✅ journalctl -u myapp.service -n 50
👉 Fetches last 50 logs only for that unit.

🔹 10. Scale Deployment api-svc from 2 → 5 Pods

✅ kubectl scale deployment api-svc --replicas=5
(तुझ्या options मध्ये नाही, पण जवळचा correct option आहे:)
👉 kubectl patch deployment api-svc -p '{"spec":{"replicas":5}}'
